  urldate = {2026-01-30},
  abstract = {This paper describes a method for assessing the effects on stocks of changes in fishery parameters such as selectivity, fishing mortality or fishing effort. The study shows how an age-length structured population model can be used to simulate the effects on stocks by changing the selectivity of a fishery, e.g. by introducing a new gear. The Fleksibest model is the tool used. The effects on the Northeast Arctic cod (Gadus morhua L.) stock of changes in fleet selectivity are simulated. The results show that there may be much to gain concerning both stock size and catches by increasing the 50\% retention length (L50) by 5--8cm from 47cm. Such a change reduced the catches of 3--4-year-old fish, while catches of 6+-year-olds increased within a few years. The Fleksibest model can be adapted for use with other species as well.},
