  abstract = {Work carried out for the development and application of Management Strategy Evaluation (MSE) for Indian ocean albacore tuna (ALB) in 2025 is summarized in this report. This work has been carried out under an LoA between WMR and IOTC/FAO, andf with the collaboration of CSIRO, building upon the work carried out in 2023 and 2024. A new methodology for the conditioning of operating models, separated but still informed by the stock assessment has been developed. A formulation of the Approximate Bayesian Computation (ABC) algorithm is employed to condition on datas wehile recognize and incorporate the unxcertainty in the system and our knowledge of it. The report outlines the current status of the MSE framework, including the toolset developed for simulating the OMs and evaluating the MPs. Preliminary runs have been conducted for a number of candidate MPs. Future steps for the completion of the work are presented.},
